,Recommended,435480,23615194,"Posted: 17 June, 2016",all,Public Safety Advisor,"If you're expecting a Trials Fusion clone then don't buy this game.Whilst the bike riding aspect is the exact same, this game is completely different. It's a completely fresh Trials experience. Combines platforming at some points, then goes to riding a bike whilst shooting a gun. I personally think the price is a bit too high. Within my 3.3 hours current gametime I've completed the main story as well as the extra tracks from the ubisoft rewards points and the secret ones. (Which involves finding secrets in game) £12 is reasonable, But the length feels like it wasn't worth that exact amount. If the game goes on sale eventually for a bit cheaper I would definitely recommend you pick it up. The game itself was extremely fun with an interactive storyline, good voice acting and funny cutscenes. It's a heavily story driven game with great encounters and an all round great game. Just as I said, it's not a Trials clone. So don't be disappointed if you buy it expecting that."
,Recommended,435480,23559272,"Posted: 14 June, 2016",all,stiggus1406 - Breadguard,"I've never played a trials game or blood dragon, however I am really enjoying this game. The theme and plot are compelling and gameplay is solid. The majority of my playing so far has been spent trying to get the highest rank possible which is really tricky. Only problems I have are sometimes the physics don't work as expected which is frustrating when almost beating your best time but then dieing because your minecart bugged out. I don't mind the platforming, at first it felt really unresponsive but after a while you get used to the movement and it really starts to flow and can be really fun."
,Recommended,435480,23670575,"Posted: 20 June, 2016",all,Cpt. Fantabulous,"PROS:- A lot of variety in gameplay- Interesting level designs and changes- Story has its funny moments- Great Set PiecesCONS:- Short as all hell- Pretty easy compared to other Trails games- Voice acting is BAAAAAADI was kind of surprised to see this pop up on steam, I honestly thought it was one of those ♥♥♥♥♥♥ rip-offs that slide in through greenlight. Turns out this is all legit and once you actually start playing the game that becomes pretty obvious. The production values for the levels are way ahead of any of the previous Trials games. With most of them featuring at least one flashy set piece.Of course the downside of that is that you end up paying more attention to the background and crash a hell of alot. In fact one of the biggest problems with the game is the fact that it mixes so many playstyles in together. In a single level you can go from driving a Tank to a motor bike to a Jetpack. Which is cool but does mean that you are not likely to get anything approaching a good time the first time through a lot of levels as you wrestle with the widely different handling of each mode.One of the other downsides to the more polished and flashy levels is the length of the game. Even with a bunch of deaths I still beat the game in about two hours. Obviously I will go back and try to ace the levels which should double the time but compared to the length of Trials Fusion this is depressingly short.Along with that the game never reaches the challenge of Fusion. You never really have to be that precise with your controls and it's only in the last level that you start to face more advanced challenges.Having said all of that there is still a bunch of stuff I have yet to do in the game outside of the story missions. There are five secret keys to find each with a clue to where it is along with rewards for acing levels.For £11.99GBP I think it is a tight little package. If you go in expecting something on the scale of Fusion then you are going to be disappointed but by the same token there are no levels in dull static warehouses to grind through. I like Fusion but it was pretty padded in some areas and this game doesn’t do that. Choosing to cut out all of the fat to give you pure spectacle."
