,Recommended,435480,33333099,Posted: 6 July,all,Hina,"80s themes? Yep. Hotline Miami references and homage? Yep. Kickass soundtrack? Hell yeah. Trials? Oddly, yes.Certainly not a crossover anyone saw coming, and definitely not everyone's cup of tea. Despite this, I enjoyed the game greatly. Lots of setpiece level design, each one is very unique, I even saw some building techniques that weren't in other Trials games. Honestly, this isn't just a Trials game or a sequel to Blood Dragon, it's a blend of both. I recommend this if it's on sale, because I certainly enjoyed the story and cheesy writing."
