,Recommended,435480,30042421,Posted: 19 February,all,Squire of Ramsalottington,"What happens when you mix Blood Dragon with a Trials game? Something awesome!First of all, yes, the off bike sections are clunky, 2D platforming obviously isn't RedLynx's specialty. But that's fine! The best part of the game is the whacky disjointed story told through fantastic animated cutscenes and in level dialogue. If you played Far Cry Blood Dragon you should have a good idea of the tone of this game, however while that was more a parody of R rated action movies this one is more PG 13, even comedically censoring itself at times.The on bike / mine cart / truck sections are quite entertaining, there's some mindfreak sections, there's cool environments to go through, and there's insectoid aliens to murderize. But you never know when you'll switch mode of transportation mid level and I really have no interest in trying to set good scores on platforming that's primarily difficult because the controls are bad (eg. landing one foot on a platform means you bounce off and potentially fall to your death). But again, I still think it's worth at least running through once for the story, it's so delightful and I guarantee it will make you smile."
